Rub the lamb with oil and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Heat a griddle pan until very hot, then add the lamb and griddle for 4-5 minutes on both sides, or until cooked to your liking.For the tabbouleh, place all of the tabbouleh ingredients, except the yoghurt, into a large bowl and stir to combine.To serve, place a generous portion of tabbouleh onto each plate and place a piece of griddled lamb on top.Add a dollop of Greek-style yoghurt to each plate and serve.